  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, COU omitted)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research contexts to predict hemolysis in centrifugal blood pumps operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The CFD-based hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and has informed device labelling discussions at several academic medical centres. A full 13-factor ASME V&V 40 credibility assessment was conducted at Model Risk Level 5; seven factors were formally assessed and six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary-condition parameters. Despite the high model risk level, the assessment team determined that the achieved credibility levels, taken together with the conservative safety margins applied in downstream clinical guidance, were sufficient to support a conditional acceptance decision. No structured Context of Use object is recorded in this package; the intended-use scope is described only in this narrative field.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset-2019",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-dataset-2021"
  ],
